{
  "spec": "molecule-specs",
  "role": "SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for the 27 context-menu molecules, expressed as ENGINE SCENE-GRAPH COMPOSITIONS (not bespoke JSX). Each molecule is data the engine's reduce() lays out into a Scene the host paints. Central, the gallery, and the Rust host all consume THIS — killing the double-implementation (JSX demo + hand-built host).",
  "resolves": {
    "23_vs_27": "molecules and styles are ORTHOGONAL axes. The engine has 23 MenuStyle layout KINDS; a molecule is a COMPOSITION (style + MenuModel + density + motion). The 21 archetypes use 18 distinct styles; the 6 recipes reuse existing styles (list / trayaudio) with composed content — they are NOT new engine kinds. So '27 molecules over 23 styles' is consistent, not a contradiction.",
    "double_implementation": "a molecule = { style, layout, model{groups[rows]}, motion }. reduce(style, model) already emits MenuPanel + MenuRow nodes + (chrome) Blob. The renderer paints from tokens. No molecule needs bespoke render code — only this data.",
    "agentic_family": "4 agentic molecules reuse existing list+bubble styles with 5 new model-level fields: risk (safe|write|destruct), badge, agent, plan, privacy. The layout strategies agentic-panel / agentic-confirm / agentic-suggest are renderer strategies added to MoleculeRenderer — not new engine kinds. AgenticGnuContextMenu is the canonical spec for Central's GnuContextMenu, replacing its bespoke JSX. AgenticKeyboardNav (agentic-panel) adds the CM-5 flat keyboard-cursor model — 31 molecules total."
  },
  "engine_styles": {
